identificationModule.briefTitle: Comparison of the Bioavailability of Metformin Between Medium Dose Linagliptin/Metformin Tablets and Medium Dose Glucophage Tablet Given With Linagliptin Tablet
identificationModule.officialTitle: A Single Dose Comparative Bioavailability Study of Linagliptin/Metformin hydrochloride2.5mg/500mg Combination Tablets Versus Linagliptin 2.5mg Tablets Administered With Glucophage 500mg Tablets Under Fasting Conditions

descriptionModule.briefSummary: The data from this study will be used to compare the kinetic profile of metformin 500mg in linagliptin/metformin fixed dose combination tablet versus Canadian metformin reference product administered concomitantly with linagliptin 2.5 mg tablet.

armGroups.label: Linagliptin/Metformin medium dosecombo
armGroups.description: patient to receive a single medium dose combination tablet containing Linagliptin and Metformin once daily

armGroups.label: Linagliptin plus Metformin medium dose
armGroups.description: patient to receive two individual tablets: Linagliptin and Metformin (medium dose)

primaryOutcomes.description: Maximum measured concentration of metformin in plasma, per period.
primaryOutcomes.timeFrame: Prior to drug administration and at 0.33, 0.67, 1, 1.33, 1.67, 2, 2.5, 3, 3.5, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16, 24, 30, and 36 hours post dose in each treatment period

primaryOutcomes.measure: Area Under the Curve 0 to Last Measurable Value (AUC0-t)
primaryOutcomes.description: AUC0-t is the area under the concentration versus time curve of metformin in plasma, from time zero (0) to the time of the last measurable analyte concentration (t), as calculated by the linear trapezoidal method.
primaryOutcomes.timeFrame: Prior to drug administration and at 0.33, 0.67, 1, 1.33, 1.67, 2, 2.5, 3, 3.5, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16, 24, 30, and 36 hours post dose in each treatment period

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Area Under the Curve 0 to Inf (AUC0-inf)
secondaryOutcomes.description: AUC0-inf is the area under the concentration versus time curve of metformin in plasma from time zero extrapolated to infinity.
secondaryOutcomes.timeFrame: Prior to drug administration and at 0.33, 0.67, 1, 1.33, 1.67, 2, 2.5, 3, 3.5, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16, 24, 30, and 36 hours post dose in each treatment period

eligibilityModule.eligibilityCriteria:
Inclusion criteria:

1. Healthy male and female subjects.

Exclusion criteria:

1. Any relevant deviation from healthy conditions.

participantFlowModule.preAssignmentDetails: This is a 2 period, 2 sequence, 2 treatment crossover. Subjects were randomized to one of the two sequences AB or BA. The duration of washout was at least 35 days between dosing.
participantFlowModule.recruitmentDetails: 18 subjects were enrolled in the original study (June 2011 to July 2011) and 40 in the add-on study (November 2011 to December 2011) which was an option provided by protocol to increase the subject number. As no significant STUDY and STUDY-by-TREATMENT effect was revealed in analysis of pooled data, final analysis was performed on pooled data.

analyses.groupDescription: The two formulations are shown to be bioequivalent if the geometric mean ratio is contained within the 80 to 125 percent range both on measured data (statistical analysis 1) and on potency corrected data (percent potency of label claim) (statistical analysis 2). ANOVA was applied to log-transformed Cmax and included study, subject-within-study, period-within-study, treatment and study-by-treatment interaction.

ANOVA was applied to log-transformed Cmax and included study, subject-within-study, period-within-study, treatment and study-by-treatment interaction. Results were potency corrected (GMR multiplied by the quotient of drug potency (DP) of Met in single tablet and DP of Met in combination tablet).
